ion Act of 1990 and affirmative action programs, illustrating the promise of increased political efficacy and civic responsibility of a poststructuralist-informed sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Postmodernism. 4aSociology : Sociology of Knowledge. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147836340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791478363423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791478363/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles